title: Ex-NFL star Alex Smith rips Commanders, Dan Snyder over multitude of 'distractions'
description: Former Washington star Alex Smith ripped the Commanders organization and team owner Dan Snyder on Monday over the "distractions" brought about by the front office.

title: SEAN HANNITY: This is a national disgrace
description: Fox News host Sean Hannity lays out why Election Day should be a national holiday and why states need to restore election integrity in his opening monologue on 'Hannity.'

title: GOP Rep. Calvert wins election in competitive California House seat
description: The race for California 41st House district, once considered a Republican stronghold, was one of the most competitive races in the state this election cycle.

title: Tom Brady talks Jeff Saturday hire, asked whether he could 'walk in and coach a team tomorrow'
description: Tom Brady offered his take on the Indianapolis Colts' decision to hire Jeff Saturday as their interim head coach over more polished veterans.

title: Margot Robbie says her female-fronted 'Pirates of the Caribbean' movie is dead at Disney
description: It was reported in 2020 that Margot Robbie would star in a female-fronted "Pirates of the Caribbean," with “Birds of Prey's" Christina Hodson writing the script.

title: Pelosi 'not even thinking' about political future before House majority called, spox says
description: House Speaker Nancy Pelosi’s spokesman said the 82-year-old California Democrat was not even thinking about her future until control of Congress was determined.

title: Kevin Durant shocked at technical foul called on Celtics' Jayson Tatum: 'I'm actually laughing'
description: Brooklyn Nets star Kevin Durant was watching the Boston Celtics on his night off, and he couldn't understand the technical foul called on Jayson Tatum.

title: The Neighbourhood drummer Brandon Fried fired for 'inappropriate behavior' amid groping allegations by singer
description: Brandon Fried, The Neighbourhood drummer, was fired from the band for allegedly groping María Zardoya at a bar. Zardoya shared the claims on social media.

title: TULSI GABBARD: It's time to talk about what happens next after the midterms
description: Former Democratic U.S. representative Tulsi Gabbard urges Republicans and Democrats to find ways to work together after the 2022 midterm elections on "Tucker Carlson Tonight."

title: Oregon's 6th Congressional District won by Democrat Andrea Salinas
description: Democrat Andrew Salinas defeated Republican challenger Mike Erickson in Oregon's 6th Congressional District, the Associated Press projects.

title: Arizona gov election: Katie Hobbs defeats GOP challenger Kari Lake, race may now go to recount under state law
description: Democratic Secretary of State Katie Hobbs has defeated Kari Lake in Arizona's gubernatorial race, the Fox News Decision Desk can project.

title: Jennifer Siebel Newsom identifies Harvey Weinstein as alleged rapist in emotional sexual assault testimony
description: Gavin Newsom's wife, Jennifer Siebel Newsom, was overcome with emotion while testifying against disgraced movie mogul Harvey Weinstein in Los Angeles.

title: Minnesota's first snow fall of year wreaks havoc on roads
description: Hundreds of Minnesota motorists were involved in motor vehicle crashes on Monday as the state experienced its first measurable snowfall of the year.

title: California Rep. roasted for comparing today’s slow ballot counting to Florida in 2000: ‘Take a seat!’
description: Rep. Brad Sherman kicked over a beehive on Twitter when he compared the slow 2022 midterm vote counting to Florida's presidential election disaster more than 20 years ago.

title: Arizona's 6th Congressional District: Republican Juan Ciscomani wins House race
description: Republican Juan Ciscomani was elected to the U.S. House in Arizona's 6th Congressional District, defeating Democrat Kirsten Engel, the Associated Press projects.

title: Arizona GOP Rep. Schweikert defeats Democratic challenger as Republicans inch closer to House majority
description: The six-term Congressman currently serving Arizona's 6th district has won election to Arizona's 1st House seat in a key win for Republicans.

title: Biden says US will manage competition with China ‘responsibly,’ no need for new Cold War
description: President Biden said during a press conference ahead of the G-20 Summit that the US aims to manage competition with China "responsibly."

title: Foreigner announces farewell concert tour starting in July 2023
description: Kelly Hansen, lead singer of Foreigner, announced on "Fox & Friends" the band is embarking on a farewell tour in July 2023. "I Want to Know What Love Is" is one of their biggest hits.

title: Idaho quadruple student homicide: 'Crime of passion,' 'burglary gone wrong' among possible motives, mayor says
description: Idaho police are trying to narrow down a motive in the slayings of four college students, which could include "burglary gone wrong" or a "crime of passion."

title: Christina Applegate tears up at Hollywood Walk of Fame ceremony in first public appearance since MS diagnosis
description: "Dead to Me" star Christina Applegate received her star on the Hollywood Walk of Fame Monday, and was moved to tears when she thanked her daughter Sadie.

title: 'Dancing with the Stars' head judge Len Goodman announces his retirement
description: "Dancing with the Stars" Len Goodman is retiring from his position as head judge on the dancing competition show.

title: Former Kansas detective, three others indicted for forcing women to perform sex acts
description: A former Kansas City detective and three others were indicted in federal court for forcing women to perform sex acts on them and others, against their will, decades ago.

title: Chicago man stabs co-worker multiple times at Coca-Cola building parking lot, police say
description: A Chicago man allegedly stabbed a co-worker at a Coca-Cola plant parking lot after they got into a fight.

title: Federal judge dismisses Michael Cohen lawsuit alleging retaliation for Trump tell-all
description: A federal judge on Monday dismissed a lawsuit brought by former Trump attorney Michael Cohen alleging former President Trump retaliated against him for writing a tell-all memoir by placing him in federal prison.

title: Stephen A. Smith blasts Jeff Bezos over Amazon's role in Kyrie Irving saga
description: While the Brooklyn Nets continue to keep Kyrie Irving suspended, Stephen A. Smith believes Amazon's Jeff Bezos needs to be held accountable for continuing to sell an antisemitic movie.

title: Mariners' Julio Rodriguez, Braves' Michael Harris II win Rookie of the Year awards
description: Seattle Mariners outfielder Julio Rodriguez and Atlanta Braves outfielder Michael Harris II won their league's respective Rookie of the Year awards on Monday.

title: Dominican woman hides $450K of cocaine in wheelchair during NYC smuggling attempt, CBP says
description: A woman hid drugs in the wheels of her wheelchair that were discovered in New York City upon her return from the Dominican Republican authorities said.

title: NBC News suggests kids 'avoid physical interaction' with the 'unvaccinated' this holiday season
description: A segment on NBC News advised parents to avoid “physical interaction” with “unvaccinated individuals” to protect their children against the coronavirus this flu season.

title: Ex-MLB star Yasiel Puig agrees to plead guilty for lying to feds about involvement in illegal gambling op
description: Yasiel Puig, the 31-year-old former Los Angeles Dodgers star, agreed to plead guilty for lying to federal officers in illegal gambling investigation.

title: Judge says FBI agent can be deposed for allegedly working with Meta to bury Hunter Biden laptop story
description: A district court judge ruled Monday that an FBI agent must be deposed under oath for his alleged involvement in coordinating with Meta in censoring the Hunter Biden laptop story.

title: White House response to University of Virginia shooting invokes ‘assault weapons’ ban
description: The White House called for an assault weapons ban in reaction to the arrest of a suspect using a handgun to kill three University of Virginia students.

title: Idaho woman arrested in boy's disappearance made TikTok posts standing in front of his missing person flyer
description: Idaho police have arrested Sarah Wondra, of Fruitland, for allegedly failing to report the death of a missing boy named Michael Joseph "Monkey" Vaughan.

title: Michigan truck hauling 80,000 pounds of corn hits SUV, kills driver, police say
description: One person died after a semi-truck hauling 80,000 pounds of corn struck the vehicle, Michigan State Police said.

title: Tom Brady, on two-game winning streak, makes noticeable social media change
description: Tom Brady has led the Tampa Bay Buccaneers to back-to-back wins and on Monday made a big and very noticeable change to his Twitter profile.

title: Student loan 'buyout,' abortion won midterms for Democrats, Biden, critics say
description: The Supreme Court's ruling returning abortion law regulatory authority to the states was key in the election.

title: Colts owner Jim Irsay responds to critics who blasted his Jeff Saturday hire
description: Indianapolis Colts Jim Irsay owner had a response for his hiring of Jeff Saturday as interim head coach after Frank Reich was fired due to a 3-5-1 start to the season.

title: 'Yellowstone' prequel '1923,' starring Harrison Ford and Helen Mirren, releases first teaser trailer
description: After Sunday's season five premiere of "Yellowstone," Paramount has shared a teaser trailer of the upcoming prequel "1923" starring Harrison Ford and Helen Mirren.
